text: 90 Urmia Football Club is a professional football club based in Urmia, Iran actually playing in the second tier Azadegan League. The club was founded in 2011 and joined the Azadegan League in August of 2018, after the transfer of Gostaresh Foulad F.C. to the city of Urmia.Transmission of Gostaresh Foulad Points to Urmia TabnakWe do not have a decision to dissolve the Navad Urmia / the team name changes Isna == References == Category:Football clubs in Iran
